I’ve got this crazy little feeling...that this is YOUR WEEK!
It’s the easiest thing in the world to worry and stress over the unknown.
-
It takes no effort to do it, and can in a weird way kinda feel like we’re being productive by keeping ourselves busy over-thinking situations and scenarios in our mind.
-
Worrying about the unknown may be our default thinking, but I believe it’s not the way we were designed to think.
-
There is so much greater power in thinking positively and being intentional about where we allow our thoughts to go.
-
From this moment, let’s be people who make an intentional and consistent effort to direct our thoughts to the very best scenarios.
-
Allow yourself to dream again, expect miracles, breakthrough and favor! Direct your thinking and watch your life begin to follow it’s path.
-
Believing for an incredible week with you!
Who’s claiming it?! 🙋🏽‍♂️
Pete @peterjbone | #achievetheimpossible

Appreciate the NOW 🙏🏽
Read this caption and follow @peterjbone for more inspiration to achieve your impossible dreams!
-
Where are you right now in your life?
Are you genuinely grateful, happy, fulfilled and living on purpose?
-
If you answered ‘YES’, you’re amazing!
If you answered ‘NO’, you’re even better because you’re honest! 😉
-
In this busy life of ours, it’s wayyyy too easy to get caught up in what’s next...we’re constantly striving for the next big thing or the next opportunity.
-
When we focus our attention on what’s NEXT, we neglect what’s NOW.
-
Instead of looking for the NEXT opportunity, why don’t we make the most of the NOW opportunities.
-
You’ll find that when you focus on the NOW; the things you do have control over, they will pave the way for the NEXT.
-
When you focus on the NOW, the NEXT falls into place.
-
What are the relationships you can build NOW, the opportunities you can give your all to NOW, the personal development you can invest into NOW.
-
Step into your NOW and the NEXT will come to you.
-
Pete @peterjbone | #achievetheimpossible

“Last weekend, I spent a couple of days in Bali sharing a slice of my story to a group of entrepreneurs from all over the world.
-
One of the most recurring themes that came up in conversation over the weekend was centred around identifying Passion to discover your Purpose.
-
To all those who were in the Keynote on Friday, I wanna make a last minute addition and throw another ‘P’ word in the mix!
-
‘Position’
-
When we pursue our passion-aligned purpose, we will eventually find ourselves in the position we are meant to be in.
-
Once we discover the WHY, identify the HOW and define the WHAT...we unlock the WHERE.
-
When you are living out your true passion and purpose, you’re not going to be in a position of stressing and striving.
-
You’re going to be positioned in your ‘grace zone’...the space where you will presented with opportunities, not because of WHAT you do, but because of WHO you are.
-
You won’t have to be constantly hunting out and searching these opportunities, they are already waiting for you in position and they have your name written all over them!
-
Position yourself for blessings, breakthroughs and opportunities by being the very best version of yourself; pursuing your passion and purpose and operating in your natural gifts, talents and abilities.
-
You’ll be surprised what’s waiting around the corner with your name on it!”
-
Pete @peterjbone | #achievetheimpossible

“Pete, sit down...Dad’s just been given 4 months to live”...the emotional true story behind @achievetheimpossible 🙏🏽
-
Come with me to Nov 2013...I had dreams of setting Mum and Dad up for retirement on a farm somewhere after living a beautiful life centred around giving to others as well as raising myself and two older brothers (definitely no small task!)
-
The doctors’ report after a routine visit to the hospital for Dad burst those dreams like a balloon.
-
Dad had been given just a few months left to live after scans revealed an aggressive 3rd Stage Cancer which was spreading rapidly from his Pancreas to his Liver and Kidneys.
-
My dream of a farm for Mum and Dad was now impossible.
-
I feel guilty, ashamed and like I had let them both down by not pursuing life and actively making these dreams of mine become a reality.
-
To reconnect and realign with my passion and purpose, I began reading quotes and writing them in a notebook.
-
I was slowly getting more and more inspired every single day.
-
‘If these words can inspire me, I wonder if they could help anyone else’, I thought.
-
On Dec 12th, 2013, I set up an Instagram account called @achievetheimpossible to share these thoughts and hopefully inspire, challenge and equip people to achieve their own ‘impossible’ dreams.
-
Today, as we approach ATI’s 5th Birthday, I know Dad is looking down from heaven so extremely proud of his legacy here on earth.
-
Even though he’s no longer here with us in the flesh, he’s in every single word I write on Instagram.
-
This one’s for you Dad. I love you and miss you 😢 Thank you for inspiring me to pursue my ‘impossible’ dreams ❤️
-
There’s plenty more to come! 🙏🏽
-
Pete @peterjbone | #achievetheimpossible

A lot of people want to change the world... But they can't just yet... Many people are seeing the world the wrong way.
-
They still see a lack of abundance.
They still don't have full belief in themselves and their skills.
They see things in the negative, not the positive.
-
But how can they change how others think and act if they can't change how they act themselves?
-
Now, to change how you think and act can be very difficult. -
It takes a long time if you go it on your own. That's why most people never change...they choose to be upset, broke, and unhappy about their life.
-
But when you have a support network and someone to learn from...you can change the way you view the world...fast!
-
Then you can start helping others do the same.
-
Comment your thoughts on this below and follow @danlok for more inspiration!
